HEADWORD: re-group
<hw>re-group</hw></mhw> <pos>v. i. & t.</pos>
<def>To reorganize into new groups; to reform a group that has been
dispersed. The spelling without the hyphen is more common.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

